hopobject.body: Can you hear me OK? prix ibuprofene mylan Jeter played only on July 11 when he returned from a twice-broken ankle. He suffered a quad strain that day and has been back on the disabled list since. He was eligible to come off on Saturday, participated in a simulated game that day in Staten Island and said today, "I guess they wanted to see some things, but for me I didn't have any doubts. I thought I was ready to go. So I played a simulated game and believe they saw what they wanted to see."
